                <note rend="inline" type="source">119.2/3006: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-06T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 6, 1935—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>245. Your 427, September 6, 5 p.m. As alternatives to the proposal to station an
                    American war vessel at Aden to relay messages between that point and our
                    Legation at Addis Ababa, please inquire whether the British authorities would be
                    willing (1) to authorize the British Government wireless station at Aden to
                    receive and send such messages or (2) permit the installation of a receiving and
                    sending set at the American Consulate at Aden for that purpose. In either case
                    it would be proposed to have the Consul at Aden act as intermediary in the
                    transmission of messages between Aden and Washington and it would be understood
                    that such messages would be transmitted by existing commercial radio or
                    cables.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
